# Cloudflare Pages headers.
# Pages serves HTML at extensionless paths (/about, /research/), so a
# "/*.html" rule would never match a served page anyway.
#
# IMPORTANT: Cloudflare Pages MERGES Cache-Control from every rule that matches
# a path - it concatenates the values rather than letting the most specific
# rule win. An earlier "/assets/*  max-age=14400" rule therefore leaked into
# umbra.css and umbra.js (the live header became "max-age=14400, must-revalidate")
# and pinned the stylesheet to a 4h browser cache, hiding fresh deploys.
#
# Fix: keep exactly ONE Cache-Control rule so nothing can merge. Everything
# revalidates against its ETag, so a deploy shows up immediately and unchanged
# files (images, fonts) still come back as cheap 304s with no body transfer.
#
# The merge quirk is per-header, so the security headers below are safe to add
# here - just never introduce a second rule that sets any of the same names.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Content-Security-Policy: object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
